cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the dissemination of messages in mobile ad-hoc networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the spread of messages among nodes, which can be considered as a social network. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the design and evaluation of a temporal algorithm for message delivery, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the modeling of a mobile ad-hoc network as a time varying graph, which can be considered as a system. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the evaluation of temporal distance, diameter, and centrality of mobility data sets, which can be considered as information theory concepts.
